WEBVTT

00:03.571 --> 00:05.373
Phoebe:
Is he going to be okay?

00:05.406 --> 00:07.007
Of course he will.

00:07.041 --> 00:09.009
We just need to
get him some help.

00:09.043 --> 00:10.978
Where's Ronald Pergman?
We know he was here.

00:11.011 --> 00:13.881
You won't find him,
not without my help.

00:13.914 --> 00:15.483
Bob: Come on.
One at a time.

00:15.516 --> 00:16.884
Down we go.

00:16.917 --> 00:18.552
No, no!
[ Grunts ]

00:18.586 --> 00:20.688
[ Screams ]
Please!

00:20.721 --> 00:23.191
Hands!
Drop the bag, Tracy!

00:23.224 --> 00:24.925
T-Lock: It's all
a huge misunderstanding.

00:24.958 --> 00:27.861
Welcome to Montana, Dad.

00:27.895 --> 00:31.199
And now I just gotta
get these zip-ties off.

00:31.232 --> 00:32.200
[ Laughs ] I did it!

00:32.233 --> 00:33.267
He's coming.

00:33.301 --> 00:34.335
What the hell?

00:34.368 --> 00:35.869
[ Screams ]
[ Grunts ]

00:35.903 --> 00:37.438
Rachel:
Run! Get help!

00:37.471 --> 00:39.940
[ Scuffling ]

00:39.973 --> 00:41.709
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

00:41.742 --> 00:43.211
Hello?

00:43.244 --> 00:45.513
Bob: 4212 Mission Street
parking structure.

00:45.546 --> 00:47.848
Bring the bag -- tomorrow.
Understood.

00:47.881 --> 00:50.684
Wolf: I installed
a microchip into Ronald.

00:50.718 --> 00:53.521
Bingo.
[ GPS beeps ]

00:53.554 --> 00:56.124
Scarlet:
Stay with me, baby.
[ Groans ]

00:56.157 --> 00:58.058
[ Knocking on door ]

00:58.092 --> 00:59.360
I-I'm so sorry,

00:59.393 --> 01:00.561
but my husband,
he was attacked.

01:00.594 --> 01:02.196
I can't do anything
for you in here.

01:02.230 --> 01:04.732
I'm not sure
that you heard me.

01:04.765 --> 01:07.401
You fix him right here,
right now!

01:07.435 --> 01:09.437
**

01:15.576 --> 01:16.877
Can you save him?

01:16.910 --> 01:20.214
I don't know.
Let me get my med kit.

01:20.248 --> 01:22.216
[ Groans ]

01:22.250 --> 01:26.053
You're gonna be okay.
I got you a doctor.

01:26.086 --> 01:28.389
Don't trust him.

01:28.422 --> 01:30.558
What's going on here?

01:30.591 --> 01:35.563
**

01:35.596 --> 01:37.731
Dr. Cowley: Gail.

01:37.765 --> 01:39.300
Gail...

01:39.333 --> 01:41.101
Gail!

01:41.135 --> 01:42.570
[ Telephone dialing ]

01:42.603 --> 01:44.938
What are you doing?
I'm calling the police --

01:44.972 --> 01:46.474
Hey!

01:46.507 --> 01:47.808
Give me your phone.

01:47.841 --> 01:49.510
Give me your phone,
now!

01:49.543 --> 01:51.612
**

01:51.645 --> 01:53.914
Go on.
Make him better.

01:53.947 --> 01:55.349
What about my wife?
She's injured.

01:55.383 --> 01:56.917
Are you serious?

01:56.950 --> 01:59.953
My husband first.

01:59.987 --> 02:05.693
**

02:05.726 --> 02:11.332
**

02:11.365 --> 02:13.601
Jenny: There's only one
entrance in and out

02:13.634 --> 02:15.369
of the parking structure.
We'll be following you.

02:15.403 --> 02:17.338
Two other units will
cover the east

02:17.371 --> 02:19.106
and south end of the building.

02:19.139 --> 02:22.210
W-What if the kidnapper
sees you guys and gets spooked?

02:22.243 --> 02:23.877
We'll have people
on the ground.

02:23.911 --> 02:25.646
I know this is terrifying.

02:25.679 --> 02:27.281
We'll be covering you.

02:27.315 --> 02:28.882
The best way to ensure
your safety is to make sure

02:28.916 --> 02:30.684
you follow the instructions
to a T.

02:30.718 --> 02:32.486
I can do that.

02:32.520 --> 02:34.288
-I have all the papers.
-Alright.

02:34.322 --> 02:37.157
Let's gear up.

02:37.191 --> 02:38.326
-Alright.
-Well, let's get going.

02:38.359 --> 02:41.128
[ Indistinct conversations ]

02:41.161 --> 02:42.563
Nice of you
to join the party.

02:42.596 --> 02:44.898
This is not
a good idea.

02:44.932 --> 02:46.066
Got a better plan?

02:46.099 --> 02:47.568
I do.
Let me call State.

02:48.669 --> 02:50.070
I thought you
already reached out?

02:50.103 --> 02:51.705
I did,
and I'm still waiting.

02:51.739 --> 02:53.241
You should, too.

02:53.274 --> 02:55.409
I don't understand.
Waiting for what?

02:55.443 --> 02:58.246
If T-Lock doesn't show up
with the money,

02:58.279 --> 03:00.748
can you promise me
Max and her mom are
not gonna get harmed?

03:02.750 --> 03:04.552
Of course you can't.

03:04.585 --> 03:06.019
I'm not gonna
risk their lives.

03:06.053 --> 03:07.255
Hey, hey.
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

03:07.288 --> 03:08.856
I'm here.
I'm coming with you.

03:08.889 --> 03:10.090
I could use your help.

03:10.123 --> 03:11.725
Just remember
who's in charge.

03:11.759 --> 03:13.227
[ Distant ringing ]

03:13.261 --> 03:14.695
Rachel:
[ Echoing ] Max.

03:14.728 --> 03:15.863
Max.

03:15.896 --> 03:18.031
Max, baby.

03:18.065 --> 03:20.033
[ Normal voice ]
Max.

03:20.067 --> 03:21.369
Max.

03:21.402 --> 03:22.703
[ Groans ]

03:22.736 --> 03:24.538
Max.

03:24.572 --> 03:26.206
Mom?

03:26.240 --> 03:27.575
Hi, baby.

03:27.608 --> 03:28.876
It's okay.

03:28.909 --> 03:30.043
Oh, my head hurts.

03:30.077 --> 03:32.045
I know, baby.
Just breathe.

03:32.079 --> 03:33.847
Breathe.
[ Door opens ]

03:33.881 --> 03:35.082
[ Max groans ]

03:35.115 --> 03:39.920
**

03:39.953 --> 03:42.222
Rise and shine.

03:42.256 --> 03:43.557
Who wants some breakfast?

03:43.591 --> 03:45.926
Please, she's hurt.

03:45.959 --> 03:51.399
**

03:51.432 --> 03:56.804
**

03:56.837 --> 03:58.472
Oh.

04:00.240 --> 04:02.042
Just a little
bump on the head, yeah?

04:02.075 --> 04:06.046
Just --
Just let us go.

04:06.079 --> 04:08.882
**

04:08.916 --> 04:10.217
What do you think, Fred?

04:10.250 --> 04:13.287
How's my plan going
so far?

04:13.321 --> 04:15.556
I agree.

04:15.589 --> 04:17.458
[ Knife clanks ]
Smooth as butter.

04:17.491 --> 04:19.159
No, no.

04:19.192 --> 04:20.728
It's all about preparation.

04:20.761 --> 04:22.162
**

04:22.195 --> 04:27.167
[ Max whimpering ]

04:27.200 --> 04:29.169
**

04:29.202 --> 04:31.439
Come on, have some.

04:31.472 --> 04:34.775
No, I d--
I don't want any.

04:34.808 --> 04:36.310
Open your mouth.

04:36.344 --> 04:38.812
[ Whimpers ]

04:38.846 --> 04:40.348
Come on, open your mouth.
Eat.

04:40.381 --> 04:43.183
[ Muffled grunting ]

04:43.216 --> 04:46.454
**

04:46.487 --> 04:47.455
Good girl.

04:47.488 --> 04:49.256
[ Muffled sob ]

04:49.289 --> 04:54.495
**

04:54.528 --> 04:56.163
Your turn.

04:56.196 --> 04:57.331
[ Dish clatters ]

04:57.365 --> 05:01.935
**

05:01.969 --> 05:06.507
Alright, here we are.
Montana.

05:06.540 --> 05:08.308
The new operation.
What do I need to know?

05:08.342 --> 05:10.043
Well, we --
I got this, Ren.

05:10.077 --> 05:11.379
No, you don't,
actually.

05:11.412 --> 05:13.647
Um, that's
rude, Jag.

05:13.681 --> 05:16.216
Alicia, please?

05:16.249 --> 05:18.018
Go on, son.

05:18.051 --> 05:20.287
Well, uh, we've got
all the precursor chemicals,

05:20.320 --> 05:21.822
and we'll be up and running
in no time.

05:21.855 --> 05:23.290
And transport?

05:23.323 --> 05:25.158
The locals seem to be
quite enthusiastic.

05:25.192 --> 05:26.527
Uh, wouldn't you say,
Tonya?

05:26.560 --> 05:29.129
Tonya's our local consultant,
of sorts.

05:29.162 --> 05:33.667
Well, the trucking industry
in Montana is...

05:33.701 --> 05:36.870
We offer them more
than living job to job,

05:36.904 --> 05:39.540
so they're grateful for
the steady work.

05:39.573 --> 05:41.875
He just needs to know
if we can trust them.

05:41.909 --> 05:43.477
Oh. 100%.

05:43.511 --> 05:45.646
Donno: We have addresses
of loved ones --

05:45.679 --> 05:47.214
parents, children,
and pets.

05:47.247 --> 05:50.518
I also have my saw,
as well as other things.

05:50.551 --> 05:52.386
Sometimes it's better
if he doesn't talk.

05:52.420 --> 05:53.721
My team
has it covered.

05:53.754 --> 05:54.888
Our team
has it covered.

05:54.922 --> 05:56.390
Alright,
this move out of Canada --

05:56.424 --> 05:58.559
I think a shorter timeline's
in order.

05:58.592 --> 06:00.160
Shorter as in...?

06:00.193 --> 06:02.229
Immediately.
As soon as possible.

06:02.262 --> 06:04.097
Sell everything.
Everything?

06:04.131 --> 06:06.066
Even the house?

06:06.099 --> 06:07.868
Why not?

06:07.901 --> 06:09.269
Clean slate.

06:09.302 --> 06:10.571
'Cause it's our home.

06:10.604 --> 06:12.773
It's -- It's where
we grew up.

06:12.806 --> 06:14.274
Puttar, enough.

06:14.307 --> 06:16.744
Your softness
is still a problem.

06:16.777 --> 06:18.746
I think
it's a great idea.

06:18.779 --> 06:20.414
I was gonna
pitch it myself.

06:20.448 --> 06:23.050
Uh, not that
my opinion counts,

06:23.083 --> 06:24.885
but I do think
a move out of Canada

06:24.918 --> 06:26.720
would be good
for Veer's health.

06:26.754 --> 06:28.288
Plus, Canada.

06:28.321 --> 06:31.258
I mean...
it's Canada.

06:31.291 --> 06:32.926
[ Chuckles ]

06:32.960 --> 06:36.564
Canada has been good to us,
but it's time to go.

06:36.597 --> 06:38.732
[ Smacks lips ]
That's right, darling.

06:38.766 --> 06:43.604
**

06:43.637 --> 06:44.938
[ Scissors click ]

06:50.110 --> 06:52.746
How is he doing?

06:52.780 --> 06:54.047
He's lost
a lot of blood.

06:54.081 --> 06:55.583
You keep saying that.
I know that.

06:55.616 --> 06:57.050
You're a doctor.

06:57.084 --> 06:58.051
Isn't it your job
to stop the bleeding?

06:58.085 --> 06:59.553
Heal him.
I'm trying.

06:59.587 --> 07:02.055
But you should have
taken him to a hospital.

07:02.089 --> 07:03.991
Mm.

07:04.024 --> 07:05.593
[ Gun cocks ]

07:05.626 --> 07:07.427
**

07:07.461 --> 07:09.429
He can't die.

07:09.463 --> 07:14.568
**

07:14.602 --> 07:19.740
**

07:19.773 --> 07:21.408
This is strange.

07:21.441 --> 07:22.910
What is it?

07:22.943 --> 07:24.344
[ Sighs ]

07:24.377 --> 07:26.246
I don't know.

07:26.279 --> 07:30.584
**

07:30.618 --> 07:32.152
Looks like a microchip.

07:32.185 --> 07:34.988
Something you'd put
inside a pet.

07:35.022 --> 07:36.924
Give it to me.

07:36.957 --> 07:41.995
**

07:42.029 --> 07:47.100
**

07:47.134 --> 07:48.636
[ Door opens ]

07:48.669 --> 07:52.039
**

07:52.072 --> 07:53.541
[ Door closes ]

07:59.246 --> 08:00.548
Thanks.

08:02.082 --> 08:03.717
[ Sighs ]

08:03.751 --> 08:05.352
I'm thinking
we should call it.

08:05.385 --> 08:06.854
What?

08:06.887 --> 08:09.222
There's no
sign of him anywhere.

08:09.256 --> 08:12.225
No, Wolf said he can
find a signal again.

08:15.228 --> 08:16.530
We've been driving around
all night

08:16.564 --> 08:18.031
looking for
this phantom signal.

08:18.065 --> 08:20.834
I -- We're not even sure
if Wolf's telling the truth.

08:20.868 --> 08:23.203
We've got him.

08:23.236 --> 08:24.538
Let's bring him in.

08:24.572 --> 08:26.239
We don't have to stop
looking for Ronald.

08:28.275 --> 08:29.777
Okay.

08:33.747 --> 08:36.416
[ Car door opens ]

08:37.417 --> 08:39.019
We're taking you in.

08:39.052 --> 08:41.054
[ Scoffs ]
That'd be a mistake.

08:41.088 --> 08:43.056
We got a signal.

08:43.090 --> 08:44.692
[ GPS beeping ]

08:44.725 --> 08:47.060
**

08:51.965 --> 08:54.367
Jenny:
You ready for this?

08:54.401 --> 08:56.369
Yeah, I-I think so.

08:56.403 --> 08:58.906
Remember, you're not alone.
We can hear everything.

09:00.440 --> 09:02.509
Looking sharp,
but lose the hat.

09:02.542 --> 09:03.777
Really?

09:03.811 --> 09:05.312
But it's -- Okay.

09:07.414 --> 09:10.183
We'll be about five cars back,
but we'll keep you in sight.

09:10.217 --> 09:12.452
You can do this.

09:12.485 --> 09:13.921
Okay, let's go.

09:13.954 --> 09:17.024
**

09:17.057 --> 09:18.391
This way.

09:18.425 --> 09:23.463
**

09:23.496 --> 09:26.299
[ Birds chirping ]

09:27.968 --> 09:30.237
I think a family of hawks
lives in that tree.

09:30.270 --> 09:32.572
You think they all secretly
hate each other like we do?

09:35.075 --> 09:36.409
You really don't care
about the house?

09:36.443 --> 09:37.911
Forget the house.

09:37.945 --> 09:39.446
He's talking about
pulling up stakes completely.

09:39.479 --> 09:40.714
Something's going on.

09:40.748 --> 09:42.750
Something Dad's
not telling us?

09:42.783 --> 09:44.384
Sandovals?

09:44.417 --> 09:45.986
Maybe.

09:46.019 --> 09:48.288
Alicia knows.
You see that look on her face?

09:48.321 --> 09:51.258
What do you know
about her?

09:51.291 --> 09:54.427
They, uh, started dating
four months ago.

09:54.461 --> 09:56.496
She worked at the accounting
firm Dad's been using.

09:56.529 --> 09:58.131
And she's got him
doing yoga.

09:58.165 --> 10:00.567
Think about that.
[ Chuckles ] Dad doing yoga.

10:00.600 --> 10:02.135
So she's privy to
the family business.

10:02.169 --> 10:03.503
Not exactly.

10:03.536 --> 10:05.338
You heard her.
She's got opinions.

10:05.372 --> 10:06.774
She could be valuable.

10:06.807 --> 10:08.308
Handling Dad isn't
without its benefits.

10:08.341 --> 10:09.810
What happens when
she handles her way

10:09.843 --> 10:12.245
into a share of
the family business?

10:12.279 --> 10:13.881
[ Bird screeches in distance ]

10:14.782 --> 10:16.449
I'll do some digging.
Yep.

10:16.483 --> 10:18.819
What are you gonna do?
Probably the
"enemies closer" tactic.

10:18.852 --> 10:21.288
That's a good idea.
You two can talk about
Alanis Morissette.

10:21.321 --> 10:23.657
That's her favorite.
Nope. If she ruins
Alanis for me,

10:23.691 --> 10:25.759
I'm gonna have to kill her
with my bare hands.
[ Chuckles ] Okay.

10:25.793 --> 10:28.128
So go get a pedicure with her
or something.

10:28.161 --> 10:29.529
That's your idea?
A pedicure?

10:29.562 --> 10:31.364
Yeah.
Why?

10:31.398 --> 10:33.500
That's what you guys do.
Oh, we just get pedicures
together?

10:33.533 --> 10:35.435
You gossip, small talk.
Goodbye.

10:35.468 --> 10:36.937
Girl bonding.

10:36.970 --> 10:38.471
You know what I mean.
No, I don't.

10:41.474 --> 10:47.480
**

10:49.349 --> 10:55.355
**

10:57.224 --> 10:58.458
[ Tires screech ]

10:58.491 --> 10:59.693
[ Brake locks ]

10:59.727 --> 11:01.561
Just stay focused,
T-Lock.

11:01.594 --> 11:03.196
Follow the plan,
and you'll be fine.

11:03.230 --> 11:10.003
**

11:10.037 --> 11:16.844
**

11:16.877 --> 11:23.650
**

11:23.683 --> 11:27.154
Okay, I'm here.

11:27.187 --> 11:28.555
I don't see anyone.

11:28.588 --> 11:30.223
Roger that, stand by.

11:30.257 --> 11:32.125
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

11:34.261 --> 11:36.363
H-He -- H-He's
calling me.

11:36.396 --> 11:38.198
W-What do I do?

11:38.231 --> 11:39.867
Answer it.

11:39.900 --> 11:41.534
We can hear you
on the wire.

11:41.568 --> 11:43.536
Okay.

11:43.570 --> 11:45.205
Uh, hello?

11:45.238 --> 11:47.207
Bob: What would you do
to save Rachel and Max?

11:47.240 --> 11:48.608
Anything.

11:48.641 --> 11:50.243
Then you need to follow
my instructions.

11:52.245 --> 11:53.380
[ Cellphone chimes ]

11:53.413 --> 11:58.852
**

11:58.886 --> 12:00.220
I don't hear anything.

12:00.253 --> 12:02.255
Maybe the wire
got dislodged.

12:02.289 --> 12:08.295
**

12:09.930 --> 12:11.564
[ Static crackles ]
No.

12:11.598 --> 12:12.766
No, they're onto us.

12:12.800 --> 12:14.134
They must know
he's wearing a wire.

12:14.167 --> 12:15.769
Jenny, you need to
call this off right now.

12:15.803 --> 12:17.370
**

12:17.404 --> 12:18.371
[ Wire clacks ]

12:18.405 --> 12:20.240
Okay.
Okay, wire's gone.

12:20.273 --> 12:22.042
Just please
don't hurt Rachel.

12:22.075 --> 12:23.743
Big mistake to
involve the police.

12:23.777 --> 12:25.712
I had no choice.

12:25.745 --> 12:27.714
Well, now you do.

12:27.747 --> 12:30.884
Take the money,
go down the stairwell.

12:30.918 --> 12:32.285
[ Cellphone chimes ]

12:32.319 --> 12:36.056
**

12:36.089 --> 12:37.557
He's not answering.

12:37.590 --> 12:40.060
All units are moving in.
Block the entrance.

12:40.093 --> 12:41.561
No one gets in or out.

12:41.594 --> 12:43.897
[ Tires screech ]

12:43.931 --> 12:46.066
**

12:46.099 --> 12:47.734
I'm on the stairwell.

12:47.767 --> 12:50.070
Go to the bottom.
Take the tunnel to the library.

12:50.103 --> 12:51.604
Yeah, yeah.
I'm going down.

12:51.638 --> 12:55.008
**

12:57.344 --> 12:58.611
Where the hell is he?

12:58.645 --> 12:59.847
Poppernak: Gone.

12:59.880 --> 13:02.282
There's no way he left
in another car.

13:02.315 --> 13:07.087
**

13:07.120 --> 13:08.421
[ Door creaks ]

13:08.455 --> 13:10.290
**

13:10.323 --> 13:12.459
[ Door closes ]
I need eyes on T-Lock.

13:12.492 --> 13:13.861
Now.

13:13.894 --> 13:15.795
[ Sighs ]

13:15.829 --> 13:17.630
Damn it.

13:17.664 --> 13:18.832
[ Door closes ]

13:18.866 --> 13:20.267
T-Lock: Okay,
I'm leaving the library.

13:20.300 --> 13:21.634
There's
a maroon station wagon

13:21.668 --> 13:22.870
parked on the road
in front of you.

13:22.903 --> 13:24.371
Keys are inside.

13:24.404 --> 13:25.973
Got it.
Heading over.

13:26.006 --> 13:27.540
Get on Highway 280.

13:27.574 --> 13:30.110
Drive 60 miles.
Take the Eagle Valley exit.

13:30.143 --> 13:33.380
**

13:33.413 --> 13:34.714
There's no sign of him.

13:36.049 --> 13:37.284
The wire.

13:37.317 --> 13:38.986
The drop was never
gonna be here.

13:39.019 --> 13:41.955
Hey, I got his phone.
Looks like he's on Highway 280.

13:41.989 --> 13:47.995
**

13:49.396 --> 13:55.402
**

13:56.870 --> 14:02.876
**

14:04.377 --> 14:06.213
[ Cellphone beeps ]

14:06.246 --> 14:09.582
[ Cellphone dialing ]

14:09.616 --> 14:11.184
You on
Eagle Valley yet?

14:11.218 --> 14:12.920
T-Lock: Yeah, I-I-I just
got off the exit.

14:12.953 --> 14:15.222
Go about two miles past
some train tracks.

14:15.255 --> 14:16.689
You're gonna lose
your cell signal.

14:16.723 --> 14:18.091
Look for a flashlight
and a walkie-talkie

14:18.125 --> 14:19.226
taped to
a telephone pole.

14:19.259 --> 14:21.594
Stop there and get out.

14:21.628 --> 14:24.197
**

14:24.231 --> 14:26.699
[ Train signal dinging
in distance ]

14:26.733 --> 14:32.739
**

14:35.742 --> 14:38.045
[ Train clacking ]

14:38.078 --> 14:41.581
[ Train whistle blows ]

14:41.614 --> 14:44.217
**

14:44.251 --> 14:47.087
[ Tape crackles ]

14:47.120 --> 14:48.888
**

14:48.922 --> 14:50.090
Where are you?

14:50.123 --> 14:53.726
Hello?
Uh, are you there?

14:53.760 --> 14:55.262
I'm here.

14:55.295 --> 14:57.197
Now take your phone
and smash it.

14:57.230 --> 14:59.199
Use the walkie
from here on out.

14:59.232 --> 15:02.602
**

15:02.635 --> 15:03.836
[ Cellphone smacks ]

15:04.504 --> 15:06.106
Okay, it's done.

15:06.139 --> 15:08.108
Grab the money and head
through the red brick gate.

15:08.141 --> 15:15.082
**

15:15.115 --> 15:22.055
**

15:22.089 --> 15:23.623
[ Door slides open ]

15:23.656 --> 15:25.959
Your knight in shining armor
approaches.

15:25.993 --> 15:27.427
[ Muffled grunting ]

15:35.102 --> 15:37.204
Poppernak: Stop.
Look at that car.

15:40.140 --> 15:41.241
[ Engine stops ]

15:41.274 --> 15:45.745
**

15:45.778 --> 15:47.180
Clear.

15:47.214 --> 15:49.516
Clear.

15:49.549 --> 15:51.018
Someone left in a hurry.

15:51.051 --> 15:52.852
This may have nothing
to do with T-Lock.

15:52.885 --> 15:54.121
My cousin was drunk once,

15:54.154 --> 15:55.855
drove his car into
a cow pasture,

15:55.888 --> 15:57.357
put it in park,
and walked away.

15:57.390 --> 16:00.593
**

16:00.627 --> 16:02.996
Look at this.

16:03.030 --> 16:04.197
[ Train horn blows in distance ]

16:04.231 --> 16:07.000
Hey, Hoyt.

16:07.034 --> 16:09.236
Looks like this is why
our signal disappeared.

16:11.738 --> 16:13.873
So where the hell
is he?

16:13.906 --> 16:17.044
Hey, what if, uh, T-Lock's
been working with the
kidnappers all along?

16:17.077 --> 16:19.712
I hope he's not.

16:19.746 --> 16:21.814
Well, let's just focus on
finding him.

16:21.848 --> 16:24.217
Okay, boys,
which way do we go?

16:24.251 --> 16:27.720
We got at least four options,
all of them grim and creepy.

16:27.754 --> 16:30.323
No, I'm scared.
Ladies first.

16:30.357 --> 16:33.360
I'll call Tubb, see if we can
get a drone to fly over.

16:33.393 --> 16:35.162
Good idea.

16:35.195 --> 16:37.797
**

16:37.830 --> 16:40.867
[ Dog barking in distance ]

16:40.900 --> 16:43.203
How much longer
do I have to walk?

16:43.236 --> 16:45.038
Bob: Keep going.
You're getting close.

16:45.072 --> 16:48.208
Are you
with Rachel and Max?

16:48.241 --> 16:49.842
Don't worry about it.

16:49.876 --> 16:51.378
Play by the rules,
you'll see them.

16:51.411 --> 16:57.650
**

16:57.684 --> 17:01.054
[ Muffled grunting ]

17:01.088 --> 17:03.056
[ Gasping ]
Okay, Mom.

17:03.090 --> 17:04.757
[ Panting ]

17:04.791 --> 17:07.060
[ Banging on door ]
Help! Help!
Anyone, please!

17:07.094 --> 17:08.595
[ Muffled grunt ]
Please!

17:08.628 --> 17:10.697
[ Muffled grunting ]
What? What is it?

17:10.730 --> 17:12.031
[ Muffled grunting ]

17:12.065 --> 17:16.069
**

17:16.103 --> 17:17.370
The hazard lights.

17:17.404 --> 17:19.872
[ Muffled grunting ]

17:19.906 --> 17:21.141
Okay.

17:22.575 --> 17:27.947
[ Grunting ]

17:27.980 --> 17:30.383
[ Thud on dashboard ]
[ Grunts ] Okay.

17:30.417 --> 17:32.219
Almost. Come on.

17:32.252 --> 17:35.222
Okay.
Come on.

17:35.255 --> 17:36.889
[ Grunts ]

17:36.923 --> 17:38.225
[ Both gasp ]

17:38.258 --> 17:40.727
Ma, I did it.
I did it.

17:40.760 --> 17:42.129
I just hit it.
[ Muffled grunt ]

17:42.162 --> 17:43.730
[ Exhales ]

17:43.763 --> 17:46.133
**

17:46.166 --> 17:47.467
[ Cellphone beeps ]

17:47.500 --> 17:49.136
[ Sighs ] Crap.
Jenny: What's the ETA?

17:49.169 --> 17:51.304
I'm not getting signal out here.
It's a total dead zone.

17:51.338 --> 17:54.040
**

17:54.073 --> 17:55.975
Wait. Hold up.
What's that?

17:57.777 --> 17:58.945
It's a car's hazards.

17:58.978 --> 18:01.114
We should get backup
out here.

18:01.148 --> 18:03.250
Take my truck.
Find signal, notify Tubb.

18:03.283 --> 18:05.051
I'm gonna
go ahead on foot.
Hey, wait. Hoyt.

18:05.084 --> 18:06.286
Hey, he's right.

18:06.319 --> 18:07.654
You -- You can't just
walk in there.

18:07.687 --> 18:09.088
You don't know what's
waiting for you.

18:09.122 --> 18:10.623
We'll be quiet,
stay dark.

18:10.657 --> 18:12.592
Feel free to join Poppernak
if you're scared.

18:12.625 --> 18:16.429
**

18:16.463 --> 18:17.664
[ Gun clicks ]

18:17.697 --> 18:23.703
**

18:25.272 --> 18:29.142
[ GPS beeping ]

18:29.176 --> 18:30.777
That must be it.

18:30.810 --> 18:32.945
Ronald's in that car.

18:32.979 --> 18:38.485
**

18:38.518 --> 18:39.752
Hold on.

18:39.786 --> 18:42.222
[ Tires screech ]

18:43.122 --> 18:45.091
Out of the car.

18:45.124 --> 18:47.727
Out of the car, now!

18:49.362 --> 18:51.531
Don't hurt me.

18:51.564 --> 18:52.699
Where's Ronald?

18:52.732 --> 18:54.133
She made me swallow
a microchip.

18:54.167 --> 18:56.135
She said that she would
kill my husband.

18:56.169 --> 18:58.305
What? Who did?
No, you have to help us.

18:58.338 --> 18:59.672
She still has him.

18:59.706 --> 19:03.443
Take a breath.
Tell us where they are.

19:03.476 --> 19:05.545
[ Sniffles ]

19:05.578 --> 19:11.584
**

19:14.086 --> 19:20.092
**

19:22.529 --> 19:24.231
Phoebe: Mom?

19:26.199 --> 19:28.668
Phoebe. Sweetheart,
what are you doing here?

19:28.701 --> 19:31.003
I-I thought I told you
to stay in your room
and watch your show.

19:31.037 --> 19:34.040
My show is over.
And I got scared.

19:34.073 --> 19:35.942
Okay.
[ Sighs ]

19:37.076 --> 19:38.578
Well...

19:38.611 --> 19:41.214
there's no reason
to be afraid.

19:41.248 --> 19:43.550
You're a big, brave girl.
I know you are.

19:43.583 --> 19:46.018
Hey, Mom's here
to protect you.

19:49.088 --> 19:50.890
You know what?

19:50.923 --> 19:52.359
Since you're
such a brave girl,

19:52.392 --> 19:54.193
maybe you could
do Mommy a favor.

19:54.227 --> 19:55.895
Like what?

19:55.928 --> 19:57.564
Well, our friend
Doctor Cowley

19:57.597 --> 20:00.367
is going to let us borrow
some of his clothes.

20:00.400 --> 20:04.036
Would you go into his closet
and find some things

20:04.070 --> 20:05.738
that could fit
Mommy and Ronald?

20:05.772 --> 20:09.041
It'll be fun.
Like shopping.

20:09.075 --> 20:10.710
He's letting us
take his clothes?

20:10.743 --> 20:11.711
Yes.

20:11.744 --> 20:14.180
Yeah,
he's a very nice man.

20:14.213 --> 20:15.848
He wants to help us.

20:15.882 --> 20:18.551
Now, go ahead.

20:18.585 --> 20:20.086
Have fun, okay?

20:20.119 --> 20:22.088
I can't wait to see
what you choose.

20:24.424 --> 20:26.893
Okay.

20:26.926 --> 20:32.399
**

20:32.432 --> 20:35.768
You're making
a terrible mistake.

20:35.802 --> 20:38.405
Think about the position
you're putting your child in.

20:38.438 --> 20:39.872
That's none
of your business.

20:39.906 --> 20:43.242
I just...

20:43.276 --> 20:48.315
I'm gonna do everything
I can to help you,

20:48.348 --> 20:49.916
and then what?

20:49.949 --> 20:52.652
What happens when
you leave here?

20:52.685 --> 20:54.921
What kind of life are you
going to give your child?

20:57.757 --> 20:58.991
You -- You could just...

21:02.261 --> 21:04.464
Shut up.

21:04.497 --> 21:05.798
Get back to work.

21:05.832 --> 21:10.937
**

21:10.970 --> 21:16.075
**

21:16.108 --> 21:18.645
[ Insects chirping ]

21:21.047 --> 21:23.650
[ Dog barking in distance ]

21:23.683 --> 21:25.518
[ Train clacking ]

21:25.552 --> 21:27.320
[ Train whistle blows ]

21:30.690 --> 21:32.158
Where are you?

21:36.128 --> 21:37.096
Bob: Boo!

21:37.129 --> 21:40.867
**

21:40.900 --> 21:42.635
Drop the money
and walk.

21:42.669 --> 21:44.203
No.

21:44.236 --> 21:45.705
No, I-I-I need to
see them first.

21:45.738 --> 21:48.808
I need to see
Max and Rachel.

21:48.841 --> 21:51.644
Not until you do
what I tell you to do.

21:51.678 --> 21:53.846
Now, keep the walkie on you,
and when I'm good,

21:53.880 --> 21:56.215
I'll let you know
how to find them.

21:56.248 --> 21:57.884
Where are they?

21:57.917 --> 22:00.887
I guess you're just gonna have
to wait and find out.

22:00.920 --> 22:04.123
Drop the money and go.

22:04.156 --> 22:09.796
**

22:09.829 --> 22:11.063
[ Bag thuds ]

22:13.566 --> 22:15.702
Uh, I'm sorry.
It's...

22:15.735 --> 22:17.036
It's a little light.

22:17.069 --> 22:18.337
What do you mean?

22:18.371 --> 22:20.006
I spent some of the money.
[ Zipping ]

22:20.039 --> 22:22.375
Oh, on that fancy,
new ride of yours.

22:22.409 --> 22:23.876
Yeah.

22:23.910 --> 22:27.146
Never had
a nice car before.

22:27.179 --> 22:29.081
What else did you get?

22:30.917 --> 22:33.553
This.

22:33.586 --> 22:36.556
Now, you tell me
where they are.

22:36.589 --> 22:38.257
**

22:43.362 --> 22:46.699
Are you gonna shoot me,
or should I shoot you?

22:46.733 --> 22:48.200
Hey, stop it.

22:48.234 --> 22:49.869
I'll -- I'll kill you.

22:49.902 --> 22:52.104
I swear.
I'll kill you.

22:52.138 --> 22:54.541
If you do, then you're not gonna
find out where they are,

22:54.574 --> 22:57.610
so what exactly
is your plan?

22:57.644 --> 22:59.879
[ Voice breaking ] You know,
everybody thinks I'm so dumb,

22:59.912 --> 23:01.448
but I'm not.

23:01.481 --> 23:04.784
And I -- I'm not
a bad person.

23:04.817 --> 23:07.053
You know,
Rachel saw that in me.

23:07.086 --> 23:09.956
I'm just -- I'm just trying
to do good by them.

23:09.989 --> 23:11.223
You gonna
get all weepy now,

23:11.257 --> 23:13.893
or can we get
to the shooting part?

23:13.926 --> 23:15.728
[ Breathing shakily ]

23:15.762 --> 23:17.229
Where...

23:17.263 --> 23:19.398
Where are they?

23:19.432 --> 23:21.300
[ Gunshot ]
[ Grunts ]

23:25.137 --> 23:29.041
**

23:29.075 --> 23:32.211
[ Breathing shakily ]

23:32.244 --> 23:36.048
Rachel!
Rachel!

23:36.082 --> 23:38.918
Max!

23:38.951 --> 23:42.388
Rachel!

23:42.421 --> 23:43.389
[ Gunshot ]

23:43.422 --> 23:44.591
[ Grunts ]

23:44.624 --> 23:47.159
[ Whimpering ]

23:49.929 --> 23:53.800
[ Gasping ]

23:53.833 --> 24:00.239
**

24:00.272 --> 24:06.646
**

24:06.679 --> 24:08.280
Maybe next time.

24:08.314 --> 24:10.349
[ Gunshot ]
Aah!

24:10.382 --> 24:16.388
**

24:18.891 --> 24:21.928
Going after him.

24:21.961 --> 24:23.162
[ Sighs ] T-Lock.

24:23.195 --> 24:26.533
H-Hey.

24:26.566 --> 24:28.701
Hey.
It's okay.

24:28.735 --> 24:31.671
[ Strained breathing ]

24:31.704 --> 24:33.339
I wanted to save them.

24:33.372 --> 24:34.807
I know you did.

24:34.841 --> 24:36.509
I know.

24:36.543 --> 24:41.548
Please, tell -- tell [gasps]
Rachel I'm sorry.

24:41.581 --> 24:43.850
You can tell her
yourself.

24:43.883 --> 24:45.184
You're gonna be okay.

24:45.217 --> 24:47.219
[ Breathing shakily ]
Just stay with me.

24:47.253 --> 24:51.290
Stay with me.
Stay with me.

24:51.323 --> 24:52.992
[ Breathing stops ]

24:53.025 --> 24:54.661
[ Sighs ]

24:54.694 --> 25:00.700
**

25:02.101 --> 25:08.107
**

25:09.576 --> 25:15.582
**

25:16.916 --> 25:20.186
[ Metal rattles ]

25:20.219 --> 25:21.187
[ Gunshot ]

25:21.220 --> 25:22.889
Oh!
[ Grunts ]

25:22.922 --> 25:28.928
**

25:31.463 --> 25:37.469
**

25:40.039 --> 25:46.045
**

25:48.581 --> 25:50.683
[ Sighs ]

25:50.717 --> 25:54.687
[ Both gasping ]

25:54.721 --> 26:00.727
**

26:00.760 --> 26:03.763
Jenny: It's okay.
It's over.

26:03.796 --> 26:05.765
You're safe now.

26:05.798 --> 26:07.734
[ Both sighing ]

26:07.767 --> 26:10.703
It's okay.

26:10.737 --> 26:12.605
[ Insects chirping,
wolf howls in distance ]

26:12.639 --> 26:17.143
[ Gabriel Fauré's
"Romance Without Words"
playing on piano ]

26:17.176 --> 26:22.982
**

26:23.015 --> 26:28.955
**

26:34.861 --> 26:36.963
Veer: Reenu.

26:40.633 --> 26:45.437
That was...

26:45.471 --> 26:47.674
sublime.

26:47.707 --> 26:50.009
It was Mom's favorite.

26:50.042 --> 26:53.980
When you played it
at the National Music Center,

26:54.013 --> 26:56.482
oh, we were so proud.

26:58.785 --> 27:00.653
Is something wrong?

27:00.687 --> 27:03.055
You don't just give out
compliments.

27:04.223 --> 27:05.958
I do sometimes.

27:05.992 --> 27:07.559
[ Chuckles ]

27:09.729 --> 27:12.364
But that's not
our way.

27:12.398 --> 27:15.702
Oh, coddling is for
pets and babies and...

27:15.735 --> 27:16.969
other children.

27:17.003 --> 27:18.537
A recipe
for mediocrity.

27:18.570 --> 27:20.807
I expect far more
from my daughter.

27:20.840 --> 27:21.874
Mm-hmm.

27:24.410 --> 27:26.345
Are we really
pulling out of Canada?

27:26.378 --> 27:28.547
[ Sighs ]

27:28.580 --> 27:30.049
Things change.
That's what life is.

27:30.082 --> 27:31.884
Those who adapt,
succeed.

27:31.918 --> 27:33.485
Of course, but why?

27:33.519 --> 27:37.523
You know, I would really like
to hear some Ravel.

27:37.556 --> 27:38.858
[ Scoffs ]

27:38.891 --> 27:40.693
"Gaspard de la nuit."

27:40.727 --> 27:42.962
I'll play it for you
if you tell me.

27:42.995 --> 27:44.163
I don't barter.

27:44.196 --> 27:45.497
[ Sighs ]

27:45.531 --> 27:47.199
Besides, I can see
you're not prepared.

27:47.233 --> 27:48.500
I can read my way
through it.

27:48.534 --> 27:50.669
Let's -- Let's not.

27:50.703 --> 27:53.005
Perfect or not at all.

27:53.039 --> 27:55.674
Just tell me, then.

27:55.708 --> 27:57.844
Is it the Sandovals?

27:57.877 --> 27:59.879
No.

27:59.912 --> 28:03.549
Then is it Alicia?
Is she the reason?

28:03.582 --> 28:07.887
You -- You do not need
to worry about Alicia.

28:10.923 --> 28:12.992
[ Sighs ]

28:13.025 --> 28:17.396
Betee, y-you came up with
an excellent business plan.

28:17.429 --> 28:22.201
Life is short. I just want us
all to be together as a family.

28:22.234 --> 28:26.438
Here in Montana.

28:26.472 --> 28:27.706
Now,
I'm -- I'm starving.

28:27.740 --> 28:29.876
I'm going to go
check on dinner.

28:29.909 --> 28:34.914
**

28:34.947 --> 28:36.783
Did you tell her?

28:36.816 --> 28:37.784
No.

28:37.817 --> 28:40.787
Not the right time.

28:40.820 --> 28:41.821
Come.

28:47.994 --> 28:50.763
I'll have an officer escort you
to the hospital.

28:50.797 --> 28:53.265
He'll stay with you
to make sure you feel safe.

28:53.299 --> 28:54.600
Did you get him?

28:56.803 --> 28:58.570
We will.

28:58.604 --> 29:00.106
What about T-Lock?

29:00.139 --> 29:02.141
[ Indistinct conversations ]

29:02.174 --> 29:03.109
Uh...

29:03.142 --> 29:07.379
**

29:07.413 --> 29:09.281
He didn't make it.

29:09.315 --> 29:13.252
Rachel, he did everything
he could to save you and Max.

29:13.285 --> 29:15.888
His last words were that
he was sorry.

29:15.922 --> 29:19.391
[ Breathing shakily ]
Hey.

29:19.425 --> 29:21.760
Hey,
it's gonna be okay.

29:21.794 --> 29:23.629
It's gonna be okay.

29:23.662 --> 29:29.068
**

29:29.101 --> 29:33.639
He -- He made some
stupid choices, but he...

29:33.672 --> 29:35.641
Deep down,
he wasn't a bad man.

29:35.674 --> 29:37.309
He was a good guy.

29:37.343 --> 29:39.946
[ Sniffles,
exhales sharply ]

29:39.979 --> 29:41.313
Thank you.

29:41.347 --> 29:44.450
**

29:44.483 --> 29:45.651
Take good care
of them.

29:45.684 --> 29:50.256
**

29:50.289 --> 29:52.258
What happened?

29:52.291 --> 29:54.326
I lost him.

29:54.360 --> 29:55.694
And the money?

29:55.727 --> 29:57.196
Bob's still got it,
but I wounded him.

29:57.229 --> 29:59.498
He ain't
gonna get far.

29:59.531 --> 30:01.700
I'll get K9 units
after them.

30:01.733 --> 30:03.102
We got them back.

30:03.135 --> 30:04.403
That's what matters.

30:09.876 --> 30:11.010
Wow.

30:11.043 --> 30:13.079
Thank you.

30:15.347 --> 30:17.483
Jenny, uh...

30:17.516 --> 30:19.852
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

30:19.886 --> 30:21.453
[ Sighs ]

30:21.487 --> 30:23.522
Oh.

30:23.555 --> 30:25.457
Uh, it's Denise.

30:25.491 --> 30:26.658
I gotta take this.

30:26.692 --> 30:28.127
[ Cellphone beeps ]

30:28.160 --> 30:29.695
Hey, Denise, what's up?
Denise: Jenny.

30:29.728 --> 30:31.563
I just talked to Cassie
a few minutes ago,

30:31.597 --> 30:33.199
and she is on her way
to a farmhouse

30:33.232 --> 30:35.134
that she believes
Ronald is held up in,

30:35.167 --> 30:36.869
and it's just her and Lindor
about to walk in there

30:36.903 --> 30:40.639
like a couple of idiot cowboys
with no backup whatsoever.

30:40.672 --> 30:42.308
Send me the address.
I'm on my way.

30:42.341 --> 30:43.575
What's going on?
Where you going?

30:43.609 --> 30:45.644
It's Cassie.
She needs my help.

30:45.677 --> 30:47.179
I-I'll call you later.

30:47.213 --> 30:51.250
**

30:51.283 --> 30:52.718
Are you done yet?

30:52.751 --> 30:55.254
Yes. But he needs to rest.
[ Door opens ]

30:55.287 --> 30:56.588
No,
there's no time.

30:56.622 --> 30:58.024
Give him something
so we can leave.

30:58.057 --> 30:59.358
I can't do that.

31:01.193 --> 31:03.896
Yes, you can.

31:03.930 --> 31:05.898
[ Door closes ]
[ Sighs ]

31:05.932 --> 31:07.533
[ Zipping ]

31:07.566 --> 31:08.534
Hurry up.

31:08.567 --> 31:14.206
**

31:14.240 --> 31:15.407
[ Vehicle approaching ]

31:15.441 --> 31:17.043
[ Wolves howling in distance ]

31:17.076 --> 31:23.082
**

31:25.217 --> 31:26.518
Oh, no.

31:26.552 --> 31:27.719
Okay.

31:27.753 --> 31:29.555
**

31:29.588 --> 31:31.924
[ Engine stops ]

31:31.958 --> 31:34.560
Wolf:
That's my truck.

